headline_main: DealBook Briefing: Say Hello to the E.C.B.’s New Chief, Christine Lagarde

snippet: Mr. Buttigieg proposed an expansion of voluntary national service programs, aiming to attract 250,000 Americans. Student debt relief would be offered in exchange.
lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg, who is running for the Democratic presidential nomination in part on his experience with national service as a Navy Reserve officer who deployed to Afghanistan, on Wednesday proposed a major expansion of voluntary public service programs that aims to attract 250,000 Americans in the near term and potentially grow to one million a year by 2026.
abstract: Mr. Buttigieg proposed an expansion of voluntary national service programs, aiming to attract 250,000 Americans. Student debt relief would be offered in exchange.

snippet: Female candidates are climbing in the polls and dominating debates. Yet Democrats are still being asked if a woman can be elected president.
lead_paragraph: GREENVILLE, S.C. — Some people whisper it, some apologize for it, and some are very careful to mention their neighbors — their neighbors would be the ones to ask.
abstract: Female candidates are climbing in the polls and dominating debates. Yet Democrats are still being asked if a woman can be elected president.

headline_main: It’s a Question No One Says They Want to Ask. But the Women Running for President Keep Hearing It.
headline_print_headline: Six Female Candidates, One Unrelenting Refrain

snippet: Fourteen candidates are assured a place onstage. The rest are battling it out for six remaining slots. In September, things get tougher.
lead_paragraph: With just four weeks to go until the second set of Democratic presidential primary debates, a handful of lower-tier candidates are in danger of missing them. A single percentage point of support in one poll could be the difference between getting invited to Detroit and being left off the debate stage.

headline_main: Which 2020 Democrats Raised the Most Money This Spring?

snippet: Ms. Harris placed second in all three polls, behind Joseph R. Biden Jr., whose support dipped. The results were also positive for Elizabeth Warren.
lead_paragraph: After a strong performance in her first Democratic presidential debate, Senator Kamala Harris of California saw a significant increase in support in three polls released this week, as she and the rest of the Democratic primary field cut into the lead that former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has enjoyed since entering the 2020 race.

snippet: The Democratic presidential candidate rebuked Dr. Scott Gottlieb, saying his decision to align with a major drug company “smacks of corruption.”
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren on Tuesday called on Dr. Scott Gottlieb, the former commissioner of the Food and Drug Administration, to resign from the board of Pfizer, saying his decision to join one of the country’s leading pharmaceutical companies “smacks of corruption.”

snippet: Seeking to overcome a deficit with black voters, Mr. Buttigieg addressed the Rainbow PUSH Coalition, founded by the civil rights leader Jesse Jackson, in Chicago.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Pete Buttigieg stood on Tuesday before an audience of African-Americans, a group that has been largely indifferent to his presidential aspirations, and promised to enact policies that would begin to undo racist and discriminatory practices historically aimed at them.
